Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.values.count

Class BitCount

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.values.count.Count
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.values.count.BitCount
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Countable, Quantizable, AsString, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Count>
    public class BitCount
extends Count
    A number of bits and various associated methods.

    The largest value represented by this number of bits can be retrieved with maximumUnsigned() or maximumSigned() and the smallest by minimumSigned(). A mask for the given number of bits (where a BitCount of 3 would return the mask 111) is given by mask(). Various mathematical operations and conversions can be performed on bit counts, including all such methods in the superclass Count.

    Author:
    jonathanl
    See Also:
    Count, Serialized Form
